Adamawa State Governor, Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri has urged the Chairman of the Christian Association of Nigeria, (CAN), in the state Bishop Stephen Dami Mamza to be strong and courageous even as he tests positive for COVID-19. Fintiri in a statement Monday described the cleric as a man of faith that has never given up on the power of The Almighty God to do the impossible. The Governor in a statement by his Press Secretary Mr Humwashi Wonosikou commended the Cleric’s strong will in taking to announce his status on a Sunday, describing it as heart warming and a testament of strong faith in God and concern for humanity. “I believe he would come out stronger from this trial,” Fintiri said. He described as enormous the contributions of Bishop Dami to the fight against the Coronavirus pandemic in the state as a member of the Containment Committee through creating awareness on the reality of the disease and working extra hard with other members to stop its spread. “Our thoughts are with Bishop Dami Mamza at this trying period. I am optimistic that he will be fine because testing positive is not a death sentence.” He advised the public not to let their guards down, but to ensure they keep faith with the protocols of social distancing, washing of hands, wearing of face masks and others as directed by the NCDC protocol against the pandemic. 